======================================================================
BINOMIAL ORIGIN: Why C(m-j, j)?
======================================================================

Hypothesis: b_k = C(m-(k-1)/2, (k-1)/2) counts the number of
'boundary compositions' that appear/disappear as d changes by 1.


p=11, m=5, k=5
  Predicted slope = C(3,2) = 3
  d=1: 68 vertex sets
  d=2: 71 vertex sets (delta = 3)
  d=3: 74 vertex sets (delta = 3)
  d=4: 77 vertex sets (delta = 3)
  d=5: 80 vertex sets (delta = 3)

p=13, m=6, k=5
